clean_endPoint_info

Source: R/clean_endPoint_info.R
clean_endPoint_info.Rd

Define a subset of the ToxCast database for relevance to toxEval analyses. Subsetting is done based upon methods defined by Blackwell et al., 2017. Specifically, this function removes endPoints that are ATG sources with signal loss, and NVS with signal gain (basically: some assay/signal combinations are removed because they target non-specific endpoints). Also, this function adds additional categories to intended_target_family and intended_target_family_sub as described in the paper linked above.

clean_endPoint_info(end_point_info)

Arguments

end_point_info

Data frame Endpoint information from ToxCast.

Value

The returned data frame is based on end_point_info, but with some endPoints filtered out and some additional categories in intended_target_family and intended_target_family_sub. The names in intended_target_family are revised to look more appealing in graphs and tables.

Examples

end_point_info <- end_point_info
nrow(end_point_info)
#> [1] 1473
cleaned_ep <- clean_endPoint_info(end_point_info)
nrow(cleaned_ep)
#> [1] 1195
